answer: What started with a curiosity of opening up my late greataunt's telivision set and knowing whats inside the idiot box, i have come a long way where i have learned about innovations,equipments and devices as much as i could grasp in my school. When i was in  7th grade a lab opened in our school. At first it was nowhere of my intrest, i didnt knew what to do in there or neither was i allowed to go there. Soon after i was the head of the lab and people would come to me for all their problems, and i learned with every problem. But my curiosity for science did not just began there. My grandfather has played a big role in it. He was a retired police officer who was expirenced in technology and communication. From water taps to car engines, we never had to call for a mechanic cause he was always there to fix it. I still remember him having all kind of tools needed to do every task in the house there was. And i was always his little assistant,  i didnt do much but hold the flashlight,hand him tools or look at some tiny places where his eyes or hands couldnt reach but thats how we bonded.
